If the sip widget has stopped registering in the control room (there is no "Registered" inscription)
1. Log in to the server voip1.swift.kg (It is important to connect via internal IP)

{code:java}
ssh 10.7.0.111
{code}


2. Open *fs_cli*

{code:java}
fs_cli
{code}


3. Set the logging level to 7

{code:java}
/log7
{code}


4. Monitor logs (exit *fs_cli* with *ctrl d* command)
If "Red Entries" are found with content:

{code:java}
```2019-12-26 18:19:30.681926 [ERR] switch_core_sqldb.c:587 NATIVE SQL ERR [database disk image is malformed]
delete from sip_registrations where expires > 0 and expires <= 1577362770 and hostname='voip1'```
{code}


So the internal databases of the Friswitch have been broken, you need to do the following:

5. Stop freeswith (When you stop keepalived will switch the dedicated IP to voip2 )


{code:java}
systemctl stop freeswitch
{code}


6. Delete all databases


{code:java}
rm -rf /var/lib/freeswitch/db/*
{code}


7. Launch freeswitch


{code:java}
systemctl start freeswitch

{code}

8. We check whether the databases have been created, if they are not, we check the freeswith logs.


{code:java}
ls -lah /var/lib/freeswitch/db/
{code}


9. If the database has been created, connect to voip2


{code:java}
ssh 10.7.0.112

{code}

10. Stop keepalived


{code:java}
ssh service keepalived stop
{code}


11. Check the presence of IP on voip1, IP will appear on immediately, after stopping keepalived for 20 seconds

{code:java}
ip a | grep 212.42.122.203
    inet 212.42.122.203/28 scope global eth0:tw1-MASTER
{code}



12. If the IP does not appear within 30 seconds 1 minute. On voip1 restart keepalived


{code:java}
systemctl restart keepalived
{code}


13. If there is an IP, we check the operation of telephony in the operator's room, if the problem persists, we check the freeswith logs and look for the problem.

