{color:#333333}Currently, tests in the application are not able to catch bugs that appear during development. There is no working Pipeline and normal tests for them. Tests covered more than 10-15 percent. if problems with tests are solved, then the number of critical and non-critical bugs will decrease by three, which will allow * the team to release every month and sleep quietly * and increase their productivity. {color}

{color:#333333}*High-quality but long and without new features* -> To fix the situation, you need to rewrite existing tests to set up a project for Pipeline. And with each new feature, run tests. It is desirable to write tests for existing functionality. Of the functionality that we have, it is better to write tests that directly affect the flow of the order (related to orders - in short, everything related to money). With the addition of new ones, everyone should postpone it and start writing tests urgently, or find one developer and force him to write tests (tests are boring but necessary ...).

 *So-so but with new features* -> don't write tests for existing code. But each developer will write tests for the features he writes. Bugs from the old code not covered by tests will appear here. But for new features, maybe (*maybe*) not.

